ry and real VCS hosting API credentials; assert a PR is actually opened and its diff contains only the intended single dependency change.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.95,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure semver classification logic with deterministic inputs/outputs at one function boundary; no I/O or cross-module orchestration is necessary to expose the core failure.","test_description":"Parameterize semver pairs (major/minor/patch/prerelease cases) and assert the breaking-change predicate is true only for major-version increments per expected semver rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.0,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is orchestration across modules: semver decision must gate PR service invocation and propagate a review flag to output. A unit test of semver alone misses this handoff failure. No real external API is required if PR client is in-process fake/spied.","test_description":"Execute scanner flow with a fixture vulnerability requiring a major bump; assert PR client is not invoked and scanner output includes the review-required flag in the same run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Rejected System because this behavior validates local gating/output propagation; real PR API interaction is specifically expected to be skipped.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
